<HEADLINE> Two Cops Killed in Jolo in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen were killed on Sunday
morning after at least two gunmen shot them at close range in a
busy downtown area in the southern island of Jolo of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened around 11:30 Sunday morning while the two
victims were buying used clothing inside a building, according to
a report of the Philippine News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Police believe the unknown gunmen are members or sympathizers
of the Muslim extremist group Abu Sayyaf, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The two victims were members of the Special Action Force of the
Philippine National Police based in Jolo as augmentation
contingent in negotiations for the release of hostages held by the
Abu Sayyaf, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
