<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foundation Set up in Bangladesh for Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Rural Poverty Alleviation
Foundation (PDBF)) was formally launched here Sunday as part of
the Rural Development Policy adopted by the Bangladeshi government
which contains integrated strategy for eliminating poverty and
initiating all-round development process in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
"We will be able to take up specific strategies for removing
rural poverty and attaining success in accelerating economic
activity in rural life," Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina said while
inaugurating the foundation at a function Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The foundation, formed on April 30, started its operation with
over 2 billion taka (38.5 million U.S. dollars), of which 629
million taka (12 million dollars) is provided by the Canadian
National Development Agency.
</P>
<P>
At least 450,000 people in 139 upzillas (counties) in 17
districts have been brought under the program, Amiyangshu Sen,
secretary of the Rural Development and Cooperatives Division said
at the inaugural function, adding that among the beneficiaries of
the foundation, 71 percent will be women.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the launching of the Foundation, the Bangladeshi
government has taken various programs to accelerate the poverty
alleviation process at all levels, and the poverty rate in the
country came down to 44 percent from 47 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
