<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unity Tops Government's Agenda, Nigerian Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Vice-President Atiku
Abubakar has reiterated that the unity and peaceful co-existence
of all segments of the society are the highest priorities of the
present civilian government, the News Agency of Nigeria reported
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a public function in northern city of Kano, capital
of Kano State, on Saturday, Abubakar reiterated that no amount of
blackmail and intimidation would make the government renege in
its resolve to ensure the peaceful co-existence cherished by all
Nigerians.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar made the remarks in an apparent response to the recent
 development of the country of which some communities are
proposing the confederation.
</P>
<P>
The government valued the spirit of unity and harmony that
exist among the societies and vowed that the government led by
President Olusegun Obasanjo would not slack in its commitment to
ensure a peace nation, said the vice-president.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that diversities of tribe and culture of
Nigeria would enhance the government's efforts to a nation of
unity and harmony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
