<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Arrests Intelligence Agents for Leaking Classified Documents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Intelligence Ministry
announced on Monday evening that it has arrested three of its staff
members for revealing classified documents to the press.
</P>
<P>
In a statement quoted by the official IRNA news agency, the
ministry said the three persons were arrested after some newspapers
had published these confidential documents.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement did not mention the details of the
documents and the posts of the arrested at the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The judicial bodies will follow up the case according to the
laws, the ministry said, vowing to seriously deal with those
violating laws.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, several agents of the ministry were involved in a
series of political killings of opposition leaders and dissidents
writers. The revelation of the cases forced former Intelligence
Minister Qorbanali Dorri Najafabadi to resign last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
