year after the death of previous mediator, former Tanzanian
president Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
Mandela has been trying to speed up the talks, which have
dragged on since July 1998.
</P>
<P>
At least 200,000 people, most of them civilians, have died in
fighting between the Tutsi-dominated army and the rebels from the
Hutu majority since civil conflict broke out in the tiny central
African country in October 1993. 
