<HEADLINE> 36th OAU Summit Opens in Lome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The 36th annual summit of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) opened here on Monday aiming
to achieve regional integration, security and stability.
</P>
<P>
Algerian President, current OAU chairman Abdelaziz Bouteflika
declared the opening of the summit in the plenary hall of the
Togolese parliament building in the capital Lome.
</P>
<P>
Togolese President Gnassingbe Eyadema was elected new chairman
of OAU at the opening session, which was attended by over 30 heads
of state and government.
</P>
<P>
Among those delivering speech at the opening session were
Eyadema, OAU Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim, U.N. Secretary-
General Kofi Annan, President of the National Palestinian Authory
Yasser Arafat and Bouteflika.
</P>
<P>
The 53-member pan-African organization was established on May
25, 1963 in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia to promote the unity and
solidarity of the African states.
</P>
<P>
The three-day summit will discuss resolutions adopted by the
72nd ordinary session of the council of ministers on July 6-9 over
establishing the African Union and Pan-African Parliament and
addressing conflicts, peace fund, refugees and unconstitutional
change of government in the continent. 
</P>
