<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cooperation With West Important: Russia New Diplomacy Concept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Russia is prepared to work hard to maintain positive
interaction with the U.S., to overcome the recent significant
difficulties in relations with Washington and to preserve the
infrastructure of the Russian-American cooperation that has been
built over almost a decade," says the concept.
</P>
<P>
"Despite serious and, in some cases, essential differences,
Russian-American interaction is a necessary prerequisite for
improving the international situation and maintaining global
strategic stability," it says.
</P>
<P>
This is primarily a matter of "disarmament, arms control, the
non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, the prevention
and settlement of the most dangerous regional conflicts," notes
the document.
</P>
<P>
"It is possible to solve the problem of limiting and reducing
strategic nuclear armaments only through active dialogue with the
United States," it stresses.
</P>
<P>
"Regular bilateral contacts at all levels and the absence of
breaks and disruptions in negotiations on key political, military
and economic matters meet the mutual interests of both Russia and
the United States," the concept says.
</P>
<P>
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov told a press conference on
the concept Monday that the Russian and U.S. presidents will
discuss issues of strategic stability at the upcoming Group-8
summit scheduled for late July in Japan's Okinawa.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov reiterated Russia has "a clear view" of the problems of
anti-ballistic missile defense and Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty-
II."There will be no compromise or hesitation" from Moscow in
matters relating to START-II, he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. plans for crating a national missile shield are "a
road toward the creation of a unipolar world." "Russia will be
required to take appropriate steps, but we wish it's not our
choice," Ivanov emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia "proceeds from the importance of cooperation
with NATO in the interests of security and stability on the
continent," the concept says.
</P>
<P>
"Russia realistically assesses the role" of the North Atlantic
alliance and "is open to constructive interaction." "The intensity
of cooperation with NATO will depend on the fulfillment of key
clauses of the Russia-NATO Founding Act. First and foremost is the
pledge not to threaten or use force and not to deploy conventional
armed forces,nuclear weapons or their delivery vehicles on the
territory of new NATO members," the concept says.
</P>
<P>
Content-rich and constructive cooperation between Russia and
NATO is possible only if "it is based on due account being given
to both sides' interests and the unconditional realization of
mutual commitments," it continues.
</P>
<P>
It states that Russia takes a negative view of the enlargement
of NATO and its new strategic concept.
</P>
<P>
Russia regards the European Union as one of its leading
political and economic partners and seeks due recognition of its
interests in relations with the EU, says the concept.
</P>
<P>
It urges EU to consider Russia's interests in its enlargement
and to resolve concrete bilateral problems on the basis of the
Russia-EU relations strategy approved in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Russia opposes the attempts by the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe to target its activity at post-Soviet
states and the Balkans," the concept says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0056 </DOCNO>
