<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Expand Strategic Partnership in CIS: New Diplomacy Concept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Russia said in a new foreign policy
concept issued here Monday that it will enhance neighborly
relations and strategic partnership with the Commonwealth of
Independent States(CIS) members for a more firm stability and
security system in the region.
</P>
<P>
"A priority in Russian foreign policy is compliance with the
national security tasks in multilateral and bilateral cooperation
with CIS member-countries," the concept says.
</P>
<P>
"Relations with each CIS states should be built on the
principle of the openness of cooperation and respecting interests
and willingness of all parties concerned, including the rights of
Russian compatriots," the document says.
</P>
<P>
"A top priority task in this connection is strengthening the
Russian-Belarussian Union as the top form of integration of the
two sovereign states at the present time," it stresses.
</P>
<P>
"Joint efforts to settle conflicts among CIS member-countries,
to develop cooperation in the military-political field and the
sphere of security, especially measures against international
terrorism and extremism," will have prime significance, reads the
document.
</P>
<P>
When building up relations with the CIS countries, Russia "will
put emphasis on economic cooperation, including a free trade zone,
" it says.
</P>
<P>
"Russia will campaign for such a status for the Caspian Sea
that will enable the coastal states to begin mutually beneficial
cooperation in the use of regional resources on a fair basis and
with due account taken of each other's lawful interests," the
concept concludes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
