</P>
<P>
MANILA -- At least six children have been confirmed dead and
many others hurt after incessant rains caused a landslide Monday
morning in a mountain-high garbage dump site in Metro Manila,
according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
Ismael Mathay, mayor of Quezon City where the dumpsite was
located, said some 70 shanties in Barangay (village) Payatas
inhabited by squatters who are earning a living by scavenging in
the dumpsite were buried under tons of domestic waste and garbage.
(Philippines-Landslide)
</P>
