<HEADLINE> Four Die in Cyprus Due to Heat-wave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Four people died in Cyprus as a
result of the heat-wave which hit the region during the last few
days and another 27 have been treated at hospitals, local media
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Temperatures in Cyprus during the last week reached 42 degrees
Celsius, with people seeking refuge to the beach and mountain
resorts for a cooler breeze.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, all the four victims of the heat-wave
were old people suffering from various health problems.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry has ordered all hospitals be ready to deal
with any emergencies and has said that if considered necessary
staff could be called back from their vacations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, power cuts continued Monday in the capital Nicosia as
a result of damage in one of the transformers of the Cyprus
Electricity Authority, caused by the hot weather and the overuse of
air-conditioning units.
</P>
<P>
The life of residents, especially the medical activities in
Nicosia General Hospital were affected by the power cuts. No
problems in private clinics have been reported.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus Electricity Authority called upon the residents of
Nicosia and its suburbs to make wise use of electricity, stressing
that this is essential in order to face the problem successfully.
</P>
</TEXT>
