<HEADLINE> India, Australia to Enhance Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This was decided during wide-ranging discussions visiting
Australian Prime Minister John Howard had with Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee on regional, international and issues of mutual
concern.
</P>
<P>
The evolving situation in Fiji also came up during the 40-
minute meeting. Both India and Australia have been strongly
demanding the release of Prime Minister Mahendra Chowdhury and
other hostages in Fiji.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed steps to give a boost to Indian exports
to Australia with focus on removing tariff barriers.
</P>
<P>
They also underscored the potential for broader commercial
cooperation and improved trade between India and Australia.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Australia's total trade with India amounted to 2.1
billion U.S. dollars and its investment in India is currently
estimated to be in excess of one billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Howard's visit, the first Prime Ministerial one from his
country to India in 11 years, caps a series of meetings and high-
level visits between the two countries in recent months.
</P>
<P>
During the visit of Australian Foreign Minister Alexander
Downer to India in March this year, the two countries decided to
resume defense cooperation suspended by Australia soon after the
nuclear blasts in May 1998. 
