<HEADLINE> Ochoa Wins 10th Stage at Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Javier Ochoa of Spain won the 10th
stage of the Tour de France cycling race while Lance Armstrong
took the leader's yellow jersey on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ochoa, who rides fro Kelme, won the 205-kilometer mountainous
stage from Dax to Lourdes-Hautacam in a time of six hours 9
minutes and 32 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong stormed past rivals Marco Pantani and Richard
Virenque on the final ascent to finish second in the stage and
took over the overall lead. He now becomes firm favorite to
retain the title he won last year. 
</P>
