<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Yangtze River Bridge Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The southern section of the Second
Nanjing Yangtze River Bridge, which will be the longest bridge in
China, was completed yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is eleven km downstream from an existing bridge and
includes two bridge sections and an expressway with six lanes. The
span of the bridge is 628 meters; the total length of the bridge
and the expressway is 21.19 km.
</P>
<P>
The southern section of the bridge is 2,938 meters. The
northern section is 2,212 meters, which will be completed next
month.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the bridge started in 1997. It will open to
traffic in 2001.
</P>
<P>
The new bridge will help alleviate traffic jams on the existing
highway-railway bridge, which was built in 1968.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
