<HEADLINE> Fresh Conflict Claims Heavy Casualties in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Monday conducted an operation to destroy a Tamil Tiger rebels
bunker line in the northern Jaffna peninsula, inflicting heavy
casualties on both sides, a government statement said.
</P>
<P>
"One officer and 18 soldiers were killed in action while 94
security forces personnel were wounded," said the statement,
adding that troops advanced from their defenses in Colombuturai
area and successfully destroyed the rebel positions.
</P>
<P>
It said troops confirmed heavy casualties to separatist
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), but figures were not
immediately available.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement said during the operation on July 4
government troops had killed at least 53 LTTE rebels south of
Nagarkovil, also in the Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The battlefields in Jaffna have been mostly quiet since May,
after weeks of heavy fighting between government troops and LTTE
rebels who were engaged in a ferocious assault in a bid to retake
their former stronghold of Jaffna.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting since 1983 to carve out a
separate homeland called Eelam in the north and east for minority
Tamils. 
</P>
</TEXT>
