<HEADLINE> Eight People Injured in Vehicle Crash in Canada's Quebec </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were injured Sunday
evening in a head-on vehicle collision on a highway about 100
kilometres east of Montreal, according to provincial police.
</P>
<P>
A 30-year-old man was driving a car carrying two little girls
on Highway 116 around 0740 p.m. local time, when the car collided
with a minivan, injuring all the eight people inside the vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The man was seriously injured while the two little girls, aged
four and six, were in critical condition. A woman in the minivan
also suffered serious injuries with others slightly hurt.
</P>
<P>
"Alcohol and excessive speed were involved in the crash," said
provincial police spokesman Jean-Marc Vidal Sunday night,
referring to the man, who will face charges Monday even if he
remains in hospital.
</P>
<P>
A section of the highway was closed for several hours after
the traffic accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
