<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Standard Football Fields To Be Constructed In Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The German Football Federation
will be establishing five new football fields in Mongolia next
year due to requests from the Mongolian Football Federation.
German Polytan Company will construct the football fields and
assemble an artificial lawn for the game.
</P>
<P>
The field will be designed at lengths of 105-110 meters and to
widths of 72-75 meters. These measurements qualify for
international standards. Polytan Company's experts will be in
Mongolia soon to identify the places, which are best fit to start
construction. They have decided to use the same model as they use
in Norway because Mongolia's weather is similar to Norwegian
weather.
</P>
<P>
As of today, there isn't a international standard lawn football
field in Mongolia.
</P>
</TEXT>
