<HEADLINE> China to Turn Over 100 Large Scientific Research Organs Into Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China will convert over 100 large
state-run scientific research institutes attached to State Council
ministries into ventures by the end of this year, as a major step
in the reform of the research bodies.
</P>
<P>
A total of 242 of the state-run research organs were turned
into or merged with other ventures last year.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guanhua, Vice Minister of Science and Technology, said here
today at a national conference on reform of the institutes that
technological development research organs attached to the Ministry
of Construction, Ministry of Communications and some other
ministries are required to be turned into ventures.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the research organs of scientific and
technological development must focus on market-oriented projects
if they want to be more successful.
</P>
<P>
The vice minister said that after last year's group of research
institutes were reformed, a number of them have received more
research funding either from local governments or by listing on
the stock market.
</P>
<P>
He said over a dozen research institutes-turned-ventures are
preparing to list on the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
