<HEADLINE> Manila to Speed up Rehabilitation of Mindanao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
vowed Monday to speed up the development and rehabilitation of the
whole of Mindanao after Camp Abubakar fell into the hands of the
government.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at Manila from a trip to Camp Abubakar where
he led in the formal takeover of the erstwhile main headquarters
of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF), the president said
the war in Mindanao has been won by the government.
</P>
<P>
"We have won the war. It will be the beginning of the
development and rehabilitation of Mindanao. That is the top
priority now," the president told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The president also said that with the capture of the 10,000-
hectare camp, the morale of the soldiers has "been very, very high.
"
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he has already ordered the military to apply the
full force of the law to those who will continue to defy the
government with their terroristic acts.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the president personally hoisted the Philippine flag
inside Camp Abubakar signaling the formal takeover of the camp by
the government after several days of relentless military attack.
</P>
<P>
With the conflict in Mindanao now nearing its end, Estrada said
he has now become more determined to pursue his goal of converting
the country's second biggest island into its next food basket.
</P>
<P>
Estrada called on the MILF, as well as the leftist New People's
Army, to end their rebellion against the government, saying the
country cannot progress unless its citizens put their acts
together and unite in the fight against poverty. 
</P>
