<HEADLINE> Gold Prices Down, Silver Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold both declined by 10
rupees (0.23 U.S. dollar) to close at 4,540 rupees (103.18 dollars)
and 4,200 rupees (95.45 dollars) per 10 grams respectively from 4,
550 rupees (103.41 dollars) and 4,210 rupees (95.68 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ready silver (0.999 fineness) rose smartly by 30
rupees (0.68 dollar) to end at 7,860 rupees (178.64 dollars) per
kilogram from 7,830 rupees (177.96 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) improved marginally by 5 rupees (0.
11 dollar) to close at 7,975 rupees (181.25 dollars) per kilogram
from 7,970 rupees (181.14 dollars). 
