<HEADLINE> Indian Economy to Rise by 7 Percent in 2000-2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Growth in agriculture sector is projected to surge from 1.3
percent recorded last year to 4.5 percent in the current fiscal,
while industry and service sectors would continue to maintain
their healthy growth in 1999-2000, the CMIE said.
</P>
<P>
The fiscal 1999-2000 itself turned out to be much better than
the projected 5.7 percent GDP growth, it said adding industrial
sector, in particular, recorded an impressive recovery by posting
7.8 percent rise as against 4 percent growth achieved in the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Service sector continued to be healthy by clocking a growth of
8.6 percent, it added.
</P>
<P>
