<HEADLINE> NBA Ambassadors Win Game 1 of ABA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The NBA Ambassadors shook off
early setbacks to beat the Chinese All-Stars 95-78 in the opening
game of the best-of-three finals of the Asian Basketball
Association League here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It was the fifth meeting of two teams. both squads finished the
20-game regular season with 18-2 records to reach the finals, and
they split their previous four meetings each other 2-2.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese started superbly with a 13-1 run as "Twin Tower"
Yao Ming and Wang Zhizhi single-handedly sliced open the
Ambassadors' defense.
</P>
<P>
Yao, a lanky forward from Chinese First Division club Shanghai
Sharks, stands 7-3 and Wang, a 1999 second-round pick of the Dalas,
is the other seven-footer in the Chinese squad. the tallest player
of the Ambassadors is 6-11 center Shawnelle Scott.
</P>
<P>
China's lead was short-lived as the Ambassadors, coached by
Hall of Fame point guard Nate Archibald, fought back strongly with
a 17-8 run as former Texas Christian standout Mike Jones virtually
dictated play.
</P>
<P>
Jones led the Ambassadors' assault instead of B. J. Mickier,
the team's leading scorer with 15.1 points per game in regular
season, who missed the finals with a stress fracture of right
fibula.
</P>
<P>
The ambassadors trailed only two points at 21-23 after the
first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The second quarter had been a see-saw game before the visitors
wrapped up the first half 45-42.
</P>
<P>
The Americans got on the nerves of the Chinese with fast-paced
attacking and a well-knitted defense as the Chinese hoopers began
to make quite a few errors. The Ambassadors closed the third
quarter 71-62.
</P>
<P>
The Americans ran away in the final quarter, winning the match
with a 17-point margin.
</P>
<P>
Jones topped the Ambassadors with 22 points and 6 rebounds.
Rasul Salahuddin, former Portuguese League All-Star, contributed
16 points. Yao Ming pumped in 21 points to be the highest-scoring
Chinese and he also snatched 13 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Game 2 will be played in Tianjin, China, on Tuesday. Game 3, if
necessary, will be played Thursday in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
