<HEADLINE> China's First Robot Manufacturing Company Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's first robot development
and production company was set up today in Shenyang, capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the Siasun Robot &AMP; Automation Co. Ltd.
signifies the start of market-oriented industrial robot production
in China, said Wang Tianran, director of Shenyang Automation
Institute under the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
The institute has become the largest shareholder of the new
company, with the institute's industrial robot R&AMP;D department and
the robot prototype factory and over 200 researchers going to
Siasun. At present, Siasun's net assets stand at 50 million yuan (
about 6 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Automation Institute is China's only robot research
and development base; its robots occupy one third of China's
market share. In recent years, more than 200 industrial robots it
developed have been used in the automobile, machinery, household
appliances and airplane manufacturing industries.
</P>
<P>
Yan Yixun, vice president of CAS, said the new company is part
of the on-going institutional reform of CAS, which aims to push
forward commercialization of advanced technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
