<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IASIA Annual Conference Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The speeding up of economic
globalization and the rapid development of the high-tech industry
have had a profound impact on the political economic and social
sectors of all nations, and pose daunting challenges to all
governments, a Chinese State Councilor said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the annual conference of the International
Association of Schools and Institutes of Administration (IASIA),
State Councilor and President of the China National School of
Administration (CNSA) Wang Zhongyu said a government has to
respond to the needs of its people if it wants its society and
economy to grow.
</P>
<P>
A nation, while adjusting to the ever-changing external
environment, must take more responsibility for the advancement of
science and technology, the buildup of overall national strength,
and for the improvement of the people's lives, Wang stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's reform and opening-up in the past decades
is a developing country's response to the fast-changing domestic
and foreign environments. It also demonstrates the keen sense of
responsibility felt by the Chinese government toward its nation
and people.
</P>
<P>
China has launched a series of programs meant to establish an
efficient and practical government, build up a socialist market
economy, promote democracy and bring the country under the rule of
law, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also present at today's opening were Luo Haocai, a vice-
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), Pichardo Pagaza,
president of the International Institute of Administrative
Sciences (IIAS), and Mohan Kaul, president of the IASIA.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 Chinese and overseas delegates are participating in
the four-day conference, which is sponsored by the NSA and the
Municipal School of Administration of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
IASIA was founded in 1962 as a branch of IIAS and became an
independent organization in 1971. The IASIA is headquartered
Brussels, with 170 members from over 70 nations.
</P>
<P>
The CNSA was officially launched in 1994 as a result of the
ongoing political reform in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
