<HEADLINE> Youth and Students Organization Ready to Convene </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Youth Federation (
ACYF) and the All-China Students' Federation (ACSF) held
preparatory meetings here today respectively to map out their
upcoming national congresses scheduled to open tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,670 members will be present during the week-long
congresses to revise their constitutions and reshuffle their
leading bodies.
</P>
<P>
Both preparatory meetings selected presidiums for the upcoming
First Plenum of ACYF's Ninth National Committee and ACSF's 23rd
National Congress.
</P>
<P>
Founded on May 4, 1949, the ACYF safeguards the legitimate
rights of Chinese young people and organizes them to join social
activities, including volunteer programs for assistance to the
poor, and selecting outstanding youth and young scientists of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The 81-year-old ACSF leads the nation's 100,000 student's
unions involving more than 80 million college and middle school
students. It has been sending college students to rural areas to
gain more knowledge of the country and to help with local
education and general hygiene programs since 1996.  
</P>
