<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Events of Robot Development in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China had invested 58 million yuan
(about seven million U.S. dollars) from 1986 to 1990 to develop
robots in the Shenyang Institute of Automation, which is known as
the "cradle of Chinese robots."
</P>
<P>
The following is a brief history of the development of robots
in China:
</P>
<P>
The first trial industrial robot was developed in 1980.
</P>
<P>
The underwater robot ("Seaman NO.1 made its first voyage in
1985.
</P>
<P>
Seaman No. 1 conducted deep sea experiments in 1986.
</P>
<P>
The first medium-sized robot ("Ruikang N0. 1") was put into use
in 1988.
</P>
<P>
A China-made underwater robot was exported to the United States
for the first time in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The first industrial robot controller was developed in 1990.
</P>
<P>
China's Automatic Guided Vehicle (AGV) was used in a soft
production line for the first time in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The National Engineering Research Center in Robotics Technology,
the first of its kind in China, was founded in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The first Five-Freedom Pressure Water Cutting Robot was put in
use in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The first 1000-meter underwater robot ("Explorer") passed sea
tests in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The first 6000-meter underwater robot ("CR-1") passed sea tests.
</P>
<P>
China's first four spot-welding robots were developed and the
first production line using them was put into operation in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The AGV technology with China's own intellectual property
rights (IPR) was exported to the Republic of Korea in 1995.
</P>
<P>
A small number of high-performance robots with China's own IPR
were produced in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The first laser processing robot was developed in 1998.
</P>
<P>
China's first pouring robot was used in production in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The National Engineering Research Center in Robotics Technology
passed the authentication of international quality system (ISO9001)
in 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
