<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets Barak for Consultations on Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met
on Monday with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak for discussions on
the Palestinian-Israeli peace talks on the eve of a three-way
summit in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Barak arrived earlier at Cairo International Airport, where he
was greeted by his Egyptian counterpart Atef Obeid, Egypt's
official Middle East News Agency said. Barak went into one-on-one
talks with Mubarak at a presidential palace in northern Cairo
shortly after arrival.
</P>
