Details of the talks were not immediately available. But
diplomats in Cairo expected that Barak would expound Israel's
positions on the final status talks with the Palestinians, which
have made little progress.
</P>
<P>
Barak would return to Israel after the meeting to be present at
the parliament, which will vote later in the day on two censure
motions including one against his plans to attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
Despite the political turmoil at home, Barak insists on flying
on to the U.S. for Tuesday's summit with Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat and U.S. President Bill Clinton at Camp David near
Washington. The summit is designed to seek a final peace agreement
between the Palestinians and Israel before the self-imposed mid-
September deadline. 
</P>
