<HEADLINE> Beijing Police Detain Heroin Dealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last week, police seized 9,510 grams of heroin, confiscated 300,
000 yuan (about 36,144 U.S. dollars), and detained four suspected
heroin dealers, he said.
</P>
<P>
This is the most serious heroin trafficking case police have
handled this year, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects are Dong Liping, a woman, and Xiao Min, a male
temporary worker with the company Dong operates.
</P>
<P>
In the scheme instigated by Dong, Xiao transported ten kg of
heroin from southwest China's Yunnan Province to Beijing on July 4
and sold 500 grams of it. Xiao, together with two other suspects
police did not name, was apprehended in Beijing on the evening of
July 6. Dong was detained in Yunnan on July 7 and was transferred
by police to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The case is still under investigation. 
