<HEADLINE> Qinghai Poverty Relief Project Conforms With World Bank Policy &AMP; Charter: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China firmly opposes the
politicization of the business of the World Bank (WB) and will not
accept any conditions tacked on to a proposal by WB authorities, a
spokesman for the Chinese Ministry of Finance said here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that in order to safeguard the integrity of the World
Bank charter, protect the interests of borrowers among developing
countries, and raise the people of all ethnic groups in the
project zone above poverty line as soon as possible, the Chinese
government plans to use its own money to carry out the poverty
relief project in Qinghai province of northwest China as it sees
fit.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Qinghai poverty relief project is meant
to help people of all ethnic groups in the area escape poverty and
improve the level of economic and social development in the area.
He said that the poverty relief project is in total conformity
with the policy and charter of the World Bank and welcomed by
people in the area.
</P>
<P>
It is regrettable that some developed-country shareholders of
the World Bank have proceeded from political motives and
shamelessly walked all over the World Bank charter by setting out
impossible conditions that will block the project, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
"This just reveals the true nature of those who trample on
human rights under the disguise of 'human rights'," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that attempts to obstruct the poverty relief project
will not succeed, as the Chinese government's determination to
accelerate poverty relief work is unshakable.  
</P>
</TEXT>
