<HEADLINE> Southwest China Water Plant Project Receives Bank Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Import and Export Bank of
China granted 6.244 billion Japanese yen of loans to a water plant
construction project in Chongqing today.
</P>
<P>
The funds were originally from loans given by the Japanese
government to China for infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
This is the second infrastructure project that the Import and
Export Bank funded with Japanese government loans in this
southwest city.
</P>
<P>
The water plant involves a total investment of 1.24 billion
yuan and will take five years to build. It will be able to supply
300,000 tons of running water to citizens in Chongqing, playing an
important role to improve water supply in central city.
</P>
<P>
The bank will also provide 6.3 billion Japanese yen of loans to
a number of infrastructure projects in Chongqing in the near
future, including a superhighway, and a light rail.  
