<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Noted Chinese Painter Dies at 89 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Guan Shanyue, one of the best
known contemporary artists of traditional Chinese painting, died
here on July 3 at the age of 89.
</P>
<P>
His body was cremated today in Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong
Province in south China.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of government officials, artists, friends and
students from at home and abroad paid their last respects to the
late artist at the Guangzhou Funeral Home.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin sent a message of condolence to
the artist's family.
</P>
<P>
Guan Shanyue is widely acclaimed as the most distinguished
painter among the second generation of the Lingnan School. Two of
his greatest paintings are at the Great Hall of the People in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He had served as the vice-chairman of the Chinese Artists'
Association, professor and deputy president of the Guangzhou
Academy of Fine Arts, president of the Guangdong Fine Arts School
and head of the Guangdong Studio of Paintings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
