<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Flood Peaks Passes Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Yangtze River's largest flood peak
since the flood season this summer passed Wuhan at 14:00 on Sunday,
sources at the Yangtze River Water Conservation Committee said
today.
</P>
<P>
The water level of the flood peak was 25.6 meters high, 0.4
meter lower than the warning line, and began to recede at the
middle reaches but is rising slowly at the lower reaches of the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Another flood peak from the Hanjiang River, the largest
tributary of the Yangtze River, passed Wuhan earlier on Saturday,
with the water level rising to 27.82 meters, leading to water
traffic control along the river, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The traffic control has been lifted today owing to rapid flood
recession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
