<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills Nine in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were feared dead after
having been buried in a landslide at Pingli County in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province since July 8.
</P>
<P>
Two days of intensive rescue effort failed to locate any body
buried in the landslide, which was caused by heavy rainfall,
according to officials on the rescue team.
</P>
<P>
The landslide occurred at 04:00 p.m. on July 8. The victims
include five pupils.
</P>
<P>
The local government immediately organized 200 people to rescue
the buried ones by various means. 
</P>
</TEXT>
