<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tropical Storm Lands on East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A tropical storm landed on east
China's Zhejiang province at 2:30 am today, according to the local
meteorological station.
</P>
<P>
The Kai-Tak storm landed on the coastal Yuhuan county, in
southeastern Zhenjiang, 250 km from the provincial capital of
Hangzhou. The atmospheric pressure at the center of the storm-
level typhoon reached 98,000 Pa.
</P>
<P>
Following the typhoon, a rainstorm hit the southeastern part of
the province. The rainfall exceeds 100 millimeters on average and
even hit 274 millimeters at some places, according to the local
meteorological stations at Wenzhou and Taizhou cities in the
province from 8:00 am yesterday to 5:00 am today.
</P>
<P>
Under the arrangement of the provincial government, local
people have been fully prepared for the typhoon. Official sources
said that Kai-Tak did bring some damages to the province but no
serious disaster has been found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
