<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Elections to vote in the
Election Committee members responsible for choosing the
Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
were completed successfully on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The elections were conducted in an orderly manner, under the
supervision of the Electoral Affairs Commission," a government
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"The completion of these elections marks a significant step
towards the general election on September 10," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Electoral Affairs Commission, Woo Kwok-hing,
said the polls had been conducted "fairly, openly and honestly."
</P>
<P>
