see electoral activities and we are satisfied with the polling
arrangements," Woo said at a press briefing after the polling
ended at 10.30 p.m. on July 9.
</P>
<P>
A total of 32,823 voters from 25 subsectors and two sub-
subsectors went to the polls. The turnout rate is 19.49 per cent.
</P>
<P>
Woo said that since the start of the nomination exercise, the
Election Commission has received 39 complaints, but the complaints
are not of a serious nature. 
