<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 10 (Xinhua) - Hong Kong stocks closed sharply
higher Monday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng index gained 408.71 points, or 2.43
percent, to close at 17,238.71, marking the highest close since
March 31.
</P>
<P>
Strong residential property sales is the major driving force
behind Monday's big market rise. The Hang Seng Properties sub-
index surged 772.97 points, or 4.83 percent, to close at 16,785.86.
</P>
<P>
Of the other three sub-indices, Finance and Industry &AMP; Commerce
rose 1.56 percent and 2.43 percent, while Utilities dropped 0.22
percent.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 13.972 billion HK dollars (1.791 billion U.S.
dollars), compared with Friday's 11.866 billion HK dollars (1.521
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index up 0.57 percent, and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp
Index up 2.18 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
also increased by 3.27 percent and 3.25 percent respectively.
