<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Steel Production and Sales Record Double-Digit Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Steel production and sales
recorded double-digit growth in the first half of this year
because of high demand caused by the country's infrastructure
development, according to a report of the latest local newspaper
Vietnam Investment Review (VIR).
</P>
<P>
During the first half of the year the country's steel industry
produced 755,960 tons of construction steel, a 20 percent increase
over the same period last year, VIR quoted an official of Vietnam
Steel Corporation (VSC) as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, total steel sales of the country,
including imported steel, hit 1.45 million tons, representing 58
percent of the country's annual target and an increase of 23
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Higher sales and production meant that Vietnam's state-owned
steel mills have officially made profits of 4.07 million U.S.
dollars while foreign-invested joint ventures operating in the
industry have netted some 10 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Vietnamese government's drive to boost demand for steel and
the implementation of major infrastructure projects have helped
push the sales along nicely", the official of VSC said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
