<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise Slightly on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) picked up 5.48 points
to end at 2,098.11 points, failing to clinch to the intraday high
of 2,109.84 points.
</P>
<P>
The market volume totaled 453.48 million units valued at 507.30
million Singapore dollars (291.97 million U.S. dollars). Advancing
issues outstripped decliners by 250 to 90 with 260 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Ipco topped the actives chart as it recorded a volume of 116.77
million shares. MediaRing was the second most heavily traded stock
with 69.33 million shares traded. It was followed by AddvalTech
which had 54.95 million units changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the biggest gainer of the day surging up 130 cents
to close at 19.40 Singapore dollars. SIA 200 rose up 80 cents to
finish at 18.60 Singapore dollars. CityMev and OCBC picked up 50
cents to end at 7.10 and 12.90 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
DBS clinched to the top of the losers list diving by 120 cents
to close at 21.30 Singapore dollars. SPH gave up 80 cents to
finish at 26.80 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 and SPH 100 slid by
70 cents to end at 39.50 and 26.90 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealer said sentiment was somewhat upbeat encouraged by a
combination of a rally on Wall Street Friday and news Monday that
advance estimates by the Ministry of Trade and Industry show that
Singapore's GDP in the second quarter of this year grew 7.7
percent year-on-year over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
However, they noted that shares fell in the afternoon
experiencing a strong rise in the morning, which implied that
concerns over U.S. interest rates hike still weighed on the market
sentiment. 
</P>
