<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market edged
down 0.15 points or 0.13 percent to close at 110.35 percent on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
 The total turnover was 51.18 million HK dollars, compared
with 63.50 HK dollars last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Opening on a positive note, the market headed south for the
rest of the day, shrugging off the latest dose of economic data
that gave further signs that the economy is improving. Today's
data came in the form of foreign trade report for the first five
months showing a sharp rise, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market seemed very reluctant to move aggressively, keeping
the seller away but in the meantime failing to bring buyers in.
The market tried to recoup its early losses in the final hour of
trading, though unable to climb up again.
</P>
<P>
Gainers narrowly outnumbered losers by 25 to 22, with other 8
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Yantai Changyu jumped 5.31 percent to 3.57 HK dollars, while
Benelux Enter added 5.26 percent to 2.60 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sez Real Estate shed 4.26 percent to 2.47 HK dollars while
Shenzhen Textile dipped 3.99 percent to 2.65 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Interim earnings reports will soon be released, and good news
will help boost investors' confidence in stock prices, Homeway
analysts said. 
</P>
