rallied narrowly except for Bond 010004, which edged down 0.04
percent at the close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the market totaled 1.18 billion yuan, down 427
million yuan from last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009908 saw a moderate rise of 0.12 percent to reach 101.57,
pressing the yield down 0.02 percentage points to 3.46 percent.
The prices of all the other gainers ended the session up by 0.06
percent.
</P>
<P>
The ten-year 010004, the only bond with floating interest rate
on the market, lost by 0.04 percent to stay at 101.92 yuan with an
intrinsic yield of 2.66 percent. It is still the most active of
all current bonds with the biggest turnover of 419 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
As the stock indices on both the two domestic stock exchanges
rose again, the T-bond market was inactive with a shrinking
trading volume. Most would-be investors still took a wait-and-see
attitude.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market turned out to be very bullish today. The
trade volume on three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
transactions shot up to 12.19 billion yuan, up by 6.72 billion
yuan as compared to last Friday. Meanwhile, the interest rate on
the three-day transaction soared up by 6.08 percentage points to 7.
1 percent.  
