The National Australian Bank slipped by 50 cents to 25.65
Australian dollars while Commonwealth gained 33.4 cents to 27.50
Australian dollars. ANZ was also 20 cents firmer to 12.81
Australian dollars while Westpac lifted by 11.1 cents to 11.937
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Miner Rio Tinto weakened by 55 cents to 26.308 Australian
dollars and BHP lost 8.6 cents to 18.85 Australian dollars.
