<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index
closed at 1948.02 points on Monday, up 15.23 points or 0.79
percent, compared to the last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume was 14.07 billion yuan (1.69 billion U.
S. dollars), 37.8 percent more than the previous session's 10.21
billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market rally, which began at the end of last week,
continued today. However, investors were still very cautious about
market expansion and interim reports of the listed firms.
</P>
<P>
A total of 119.609 million shares changed hands today. Market
gainers outnumbered losers by 271 to 215, with another 8 stock
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Lingyuan Steel, Heilongjiang Electric Power Co. Ltd and
Xinjiang Friendship Co. Ltd were the top three gainers today, as
their prices hit the 10 percent daily limit. The unit price of
Xinjiang Friendship Co. Ltd soared 10.03 percent to 16.56 yuan,
that of Heilongjiang Electric Power Co Ltd rose 10.02 percent to
15.81 yuan and that of Lingyuan Steel gained 10 percent to close
at 11.11 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that the listed iron and steel companies are
expected to report over 10 percent increase in their interim
performance reports.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Malong chemicals &AMP; Construction Co. Ltd was the biggest
loser today with its price plunging 10.02 percent to close at 21.
38 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high tomorrow, Homeway
analysts predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
