<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Edges Up on Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index
closed at 605.80 points on Monday, up 4.13 points or 0.69 percent
from the last close. The sub-index closed at 4723.47 points, down
29.56 points from Friday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover stood at 13.37 billion yuan (1.61 billion U.S.
dollars), 29.92 percent more than Friday's 9.36 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The market edged up on Monday, buoyed up by positive news from
the National Bureau of Statistics that the economy is expanding.
However, investors were still cautious about market expansion and
listed companies' interim reports, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market winners beat losers by 292 to 182, with prices of
other 4 stocks unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi Guitang (Group) Co. Ltd was the top gainer with its
price jumping 8.63 percent to 11.20 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
China Southern Glass Holding Co. Ltd was the biggest loser,
with price dropping 7.09 percent to 22.42 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is expected to fluctuate within a narrow range
tomorrow if there is no stimuli, Homeway analysts predicted.
</P>
</TEXT>
