Egyptian Natural Gas Company (GASCO) has signed a contract with the
British-U.S. giant BP Amoco for the export of Egyptian propane gas.
Under the deal, BP Amoco would buy 80,000 tons of propane, worth 25
million U.S. dollars, from El Amria Natural Gases Complex,
affiliated to GASCO, during the fiscal year 2000/2001. This is the
first time that Egypt has exported propane.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa arrived in Lome late
Sunday on a three-day visit to Togo. During his stay, Moussa will
attend the meeting of the 36th session of the African summit to
kick off Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak Sunday held talks with
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat at Borg el-Arab near Alexandria to
discuss Tuesday's Camp David summit, aimed at removing obstacles
blocking a final Israeli-Palestinian peace deal.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said the talks had focused on the
status of Jerusalem, which he said was the most urgent issue on the
summit's agenda. 
</P>
