<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Possible to Lift Fish Ban on Uganda in July  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) might lift
its ban on Ugandan fish export this month, the Monitor daily
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
An EU veterinary committee will sit this month to consider the
ban which was imposed on Uganda's fish export to the EU since
March 1999.
</P>
<P>
"There is a proposal by some member states to consider lifting
the ban, and what is envisaged is that the issue may be considered,
" said Ryelendt Bernad, head of an inspection team of the EU on
the issue.
</P>
<P>
Bernad said that lifting the ban is the most immediate, and
this is the long term issue of a definite monitoring
infrastructure to ensure that incidents like fish poisoning do not
occur again.
</P>
<P>
Ugandans used poison to harvest fish in early 1999, which
resulted in the ban on Uganda's fish export to the EU.
</P>
<P>
The EU threatened that if Uganda could not meet the new demands
by December 23, 2000, it would be permanently ruled out of the
list of countries allowed to export fish to the EU.
</P>
<P>
The EU's ban on Uganda's fish export reduced the country's
earnings by more than 30 million U.S. dollars over the past year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
