WELLINGTON -- The New Zealand government has contributed a
total of 466,000 NZ dollars (219,500 U.S. dollars) to Red Cross
societies in response to humanitarian needs arising from the
Solomon Islands and Fiji crises.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Associate Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade
Matt Robson Monday announced in a government press release that a
grant of 216,000 NZ dollars (102,000 U.S. dollars) will be given
to the New Zealand Red Cross to assist with the purchase of
essential pharmaceutical supplies for Solomon Islands health
services. This will supplement a previously announced grant of 150,
000 NZ dollars (70,500 U.S. dollars) to support capacity building
for the Solomon Islands Red Cross. (New Zealand-Red Cross)
