<HEADLINE> Iranian President Leaves for Germany on Landmark Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
left here on Monday for the German capital Berlin on a landmark
three-day state visit.
</P>
<P>
The visit, taking place at the invitation of German Federal
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, is the first by an Iranian president
since the 1979 Islamic revolution, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
"Iran-Germany ties have witnessed many ups and downs in recent
years and the Islamic Republic of Iran, based on its policy of
detente and by adopting appropriate measures for an active
diplomacy, tries to seize suitable opportunities," Khatami told
reporters before his departure at the Mehrabad Airport.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany is an outstanding member in the European Union
(EU), and there are many areas for bilateral cooperation between
Tehran and Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi and a number of presidential
advisors are accompanying the president on his visit, which is
expected to further enhance the relations between Iran and the EU.
</P>
