<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore's GDP Estimated to Grow by 7.7 Pct in 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Advance estimates show That
Singapore's GDP grew 7.7 percent in the Second quarter 2000 year-
on-year, lower than the 9.2 percent for the previous quarter,
according to a press release from the Ministry of Trade and
Industry (MTI).
</P>
<P>
The goods-producing industries is estimated to have grown by 7.
8 percent over the same period last year, higher than 6.6 percent
growth in the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
The Manufacturing sector, continued its robust growth, boosted
by the electronics and chemical industries, while the construction
sector remained sluggish.
</P>
<P>
The services-producing industries is estimated to have posted a
6.8 percent year-on-year growth, lower than the 9.4 percent growth
registered in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Most sectors of the services industries experienced healthy
growth with the financial services estimated to have declined due
largely to the high base last year, MTI said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
