<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Responds to Humanitarian Need in Solomons, Fiji </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand government has
contributed a total of 466,000 NZ dollars (219,500 U.S. dollars)
to Red Cross societies in response to humanitarian needs arising
from the Solomon Islands and Fiji crises.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand Associate Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade
Matt Robson Monday announced in a government press release that a
grant of 216,000 NZ dollars (102,000 U.S. dollars) will be given
to the New Zealand Red Cross to assist with the purchase of
essential pharmaceutical supplies for Solomon Islands health
services.
</P>
<P>
This will supplement a previously announced grant of 150,000 NZ
dollars (70,500 U.S. dollars) to support capacity building for the
Solomon Islands Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
The associate minister also announced a 100,000 NZ dollars (47,
000 U.S. dollars) assistance to the Fiji Red Cross with additional
expenses incurred during the hostage crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
