<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.6 on
Richter scale jolted the mountain pass of the Tanggula Range in
Tibet Autonomous Region at 12:25 (Beijing time) today.
</P>
<P>
According to China Seismological Bureau, the epicenter of the
quake is located at 32.9 degrees north latitude and 92.3 degrees
east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The quake-hit area is sparsely populated and information about
damages are not available at press time.  
</P>
