<HEADLINE> Nepal, India Promote Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KATHMANDU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Minister for Industry,
Commerce and Supplies Ram Krishna Tamrakar held official talks
here Sunday with visiting Indian Minister of State for Railways
Digvijaya Singh.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued Monday by Ministry of Industry,
Commerce and Supplies said that the talks were aimed at further
deepening the friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Trade problems between Nepal and India, additional customs
tariff imposed on Nepali products by India and the promotion of
joint investment were discussed during the talks, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The talks had also discussed the project of extending railways
from India to the areas of Nepal that borders India, it said.
</P>
<P>
Singh arrived here Sunday to take part in the foundation stone-
laying ceremony of the railway line from Raxaul of India to
Birgunj, a border city of Nepal. 
</P>
