<HEADLINE> Iraq and Bangladesh Lead in Asia U-19 Football Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Group favorites Iraqis maintained
their scoring spree after routing Maldives 6-0 in the 32nd Asian
Youth (Under-19) Football Championship qualifiers Sunday at
Rajshahi, northwest Bangladesh, The Independent newspaper
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Iraq, who opened their campaign with a facile 7-0 win over
Nepal, led the first half 2-0 in this purely one-sided match.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's another match, the host Bangladesh blanked Nepal 2-
0 to keep their hopes alive to qualify for the finals of the
Championship from Group-4. Bangladesh trounced Maldives 4-1 in
their opening match.
</P>
<P>
Both Bangladesh and Iraq are on six points and the hosts must
win to topple Iraq in the last match tomorrow to book the final-
round berth in Iran. Iraqis who have a superior goal difference,
need only a draw to advance from Group-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
