<HEADLINE> US, DPRK Resume Talks in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The US is represented by Robert Einhorn, Assistant Secretary of
State for non-proliferation, and the DPRK delegation is headed by
Jang Chang Chon, director-general for US affairs at the foreign
ministry.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled three-day meeting is being held at the US embassy
here and is expected to cover a wide range of issues, including US
concerns over DPRK's missiles programs.
</P>
<P>
This is the second meeting between the US and the DPRK in Kuala
Lumpur.
</P>
<P>
A month ago, the two sides held talks here for a different
purpose. Their June meeting was to renew their bilateral
discussions on the accounting of American servicemen missing in
action during the Korean War.
</P>
<P>
The latest US-DPRK Korea meeting is expected to bring some
positive development following the historic summit between South
Korean President Kim Dae-jung and his DPRK counterpart Kim Jong Il
in Pyongyang from June 13 to 15. 
