<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cooperates with US in Copyright Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGDONG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China is cooperating with the
United States in combating rampant copyright infringement in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Xu Chao, deputy director of the Copyright Department of the
State Copyright Bureau, said that China has always been spreading
information on copyright protection among its people, and the
United States can do a lot in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bureau launched a training course with reputed
U.S. copyright institutes, including the Business Software
Alliance, the Software and Information Industry Association and
the United States Information Technology Office, in south China's
Guangdong province recently.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong had been regarded as the No.1 producer of pirated
VCDs and software.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 Chinese lawyers, businessmen and officials
attended the course, and discussed international norms concerning
the protection of copyright.
</P>
<P>
Xu said China will hold similar training courses in other parts
of China, and more foreign experts would be invited.
</P>
<P>
He also disclosed that relevant departments of China are
working to revise the country's copyright law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
