<HEADLINE> Morocco Beats Algeria 2-1 in World Cup Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, Morocco, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Morocco took a 2-1 win over
Algeria on Sunday in its Group 3 match in Africa's 2002 World Cup
qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Algerians controlled the tough, physical game by scoring in
the 36th minute by Ali Ben Sahib from a cross delivered by
midfielder Abdelhafid Tassout.
</P>
<P>
Both teams came into Sunday's match with a draw from their
first outings. Only the winner of the group, which also includes
Egypt, Senegal and Namibia, goes through to the World Cup finals
in South Korea and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Morocco gave the 12,000 spectators in the Fez stadium something
to cheer about in the second half, coming back much stronger
especially in midfield where Youssef Chipo led the revival.
</P>
<P>
In the 49th minute, Abdeljalil Camacho equalized. He struck
home his second in the 75th minute. Algeria never got back into
the game. 
</P>
