<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Area to Close 800 Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China will shut down 800
enterprises in the Three Gorges areas in three years, which are
losing money and producing heavy pollution.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises, collective-owned companies and
individual firms each make up one third of the total, according to
local official sources.
</P>
<P>
According to state policies, enterprises in the Three Gorges
areas that are big polluters and losing money in management are to
be closed down instead of moving to other places.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,500 enterprises in the Three Gorges Dam area are
to be relocated to make way for the construction of the Dam, with
more than one million people to be immigrated.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Dam, the largest in the world to generate
electricity and combat flood, is to be completed in 2008
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the 800 shut-down enterprises with 90,
000 employees, can get a compensation premium of 2 billion yuan
from the state, and the money will be first used for resettling
the laid-off workers and helping them find new jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
