<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Menace Henan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Many rivers in central China's
Henan Province are in danger of flooding, as the water in some
reservoirs is at dangerous levels, according to sources at the
flood control authority of Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province has received heavy rainfall for several days and
the floods have inundated 5,800 houses and 86,000 ha.of farmland
so far, according to initial statistics. There are no reports of
casualties as yet.
</P>
<P>
Some 118 villages in Pingdingshan City in the province are
trapped by rising floodwaters, and in Nanyang City traffic has
been paralyzed for the same reason.
</P>
<P>
Some four million local residents have been mobilized to
reinforce dykes and examine dangerous sections of the main
embankments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
