<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Million Large Yellow Croakers Released into Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China has released 1.1 million
fry of large yellow croakers into the East China Sea this year to
help increase their numbers.
</P>
<P>
Most of them are six-seven cm and 3,000 of them are as long as
15 cm.
</P>
<P>
About 300,000 fry have been sent to the Zhoushan sea area,
China's largest fishing ground, off Zhejiang Province. The rest
went to nearby Xiangshan Bay.
</P>
<P>
The large yellow croaker was abundant in the 1970s, but
excessive fishing in the '80s and marine pollution in the '90s
sharply reduced their numbers and nearly left them extinct.
</P>
<P>
Since 1998 a total of 450,000 artificially-bred croakers have
been let go into the East China Sea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
