<HEADLINE> Northern Border City Attracts Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's largest land port city of
Manzhouli in Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region signed agreements on
45 cooperative projects with investors from both home and abroad
in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The total funding for the projects is 41 million yuan, eight
times the figure from the same period last year, an official
source said.
</P>
<P>
The projects cover sectors of infrastructure, industry, real
estate, and commerce, said Yang Hanzhong, the mayor of Manzhouli.
</P>
<P>
The investment boost to the city's economic development is
expected to continue in the second half of this year, Yang said,
adding that at least four projects involving 40 million yuan each
will be signed in the period.
</P>
<P>
Located along China's northern border with both Mongolia and
Russia, Manzhouli is now playing an increasingly more important
role in trade with Asian and European countries.  
</P>
