<HEADLINE> China's Industry Grows 11.2 Percent in Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial output grew by
11.2 percent over the same period of last year in the first half
of this year, registering the highest half-year growth rate in the
past three years.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS)
today showed that industrial added-value totaled 1.0996 trillion
yuan (132.5 billion US dollars) during January to June.  
</P>
</TEXT>
