<HEADLINE> Women's Doubles Final Delayed Until Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LONDON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The women's doubles final of the
Wimbledon tennis championships is rescheduled to play at 1100 GMT
Monday after rain interrupted the program on Sunday, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
The final is between American sisters Serena and Venus Williams
and Julie Halard-Decugis of France and Ai Sugiyama of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Venus Williams won the women's singles title by beating Lindsay
Davenport on Saturday. 
</P>
