<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rainstorms Kill 35, Ruin Crops in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains that drummed northwest
China's Shaanxi Province in recent days greatly eased the months-
long drought, but at the same time caused hundreds of millions of
yuan in economic disaster, affecting a dozen counties.
</P>
<P>
Heavy rain and hail storms which hit Ankang Prefecture in
southern Shaanxi in late June killed 35 people and damaged 70,000
hectares of crops, 10,000 hectares of which were ruined.
</P>
<P>
The rainstorms also destroyed many rural residential houses
and a large area of arable land.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has experienced serious drought for five consecutive
months this year, with one million hectares of farmland choked dry
by the drought and some 10,000 hectares of summer crops dried out
and produced nothing.
</P>
<P>
Rain has fallen steadily on this northwest China province since
the beginning of June. But heavy rain and hails in some areas have
brought about even greater disaster than the drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
