<HEADLINE> Liberian Rebels Make New Advances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Liberian government Monday said
that insurgents from neighboring Guinea have made new advances in
the north of the country, occupying part of the main provincial
town of Voinjama.
</P>
<P>
Liberian Information Minister Joe Mulbah was quoted by the
British Broadcast Corporation as saying in the capital Monrovia
that Liberia's armed forces were moving swiftly against the
dissident forces.
</P>
<P>
The insurgents entered Liberia from Guinea, he said, accusing
Guinea of arming and training them as well.
</P>
<P>
According to Mulbah, Monrovia has sent a protest to Guinea, as
well as to the Organization of African Unity and the United
Nations about this.
</P>
<P>
The Liberian military would chase the dissident forces to their
hideouts and destroy them, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
