<DOCNO> XIE20000710.0306 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech President Signs Law on Electronic Signatures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Czech President Vaclav Havel on
Monday signed a law which makes electronic signatures the same
status as hand-written ones, the Czech News Agency quoted
Presidential Office spokesman Martin Krafl as saying.
</P>
<P>
The bill initiators say that the law will simplify the
communication with state authorities and make it easier for both
companies and consumers to do business online.
</P>
<P>
Both houses of parliament passed the law several days ago. The
Czech Republic is the first country in central and eastern Europe
to pass such a law.
</P>
<P>
Under the law, digital certificate providers will be
responsible for online security and will be supervised by the
Office for Protection of Personal Data. Electronic signature
software is to be provided to interested computer users by digital
certificate providers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
