<HEADLINE> Brazil's Exports to Mexico Go Up 100 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's exports to Mexico went
up over 100 percent in the first five weeks of year 2000, with a
total volume of 640 million U.S. dollars, "Mercantile Gazette"
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, according to the newspaper, Mexico's exports to
Brazil in the same period came to 265 million dollars, with a
growth of barely 18 percent over 1999' s same lapse.
</P>
<P>
Brazil had obtained until May a trade surplus of 376 million
dollars with Mexico, surpassing the 94 million dollar balance in
favor of Brazil obtained between January and May 1999.
</P>
<P>
The rapid increase of Brazil's exports to Mexico was mainly by
sales of cars, vehicle motors, car parts and cellular phones,
making Mexico one of the most dynamic markets for products made in
Brazil. 
</P>
