<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed With Dow Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Monday with the Dow Jones industrial average rising but the Nasdaq
composite falling.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Dow index rose 10.60 at 10,646.58
and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 42.91 at 3,
980.29.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index fell 3.28 at 1,475.62.
</P>
<P>
The market performed cautiously as investors were waiting for a
rush of corporate earnings reports in the second quarter, which
will come out later this week.
</P>
<P>
While most of analysts believed that the latest signals of the
slowdown in the U.S. economy would prompt the Federal Reserve to
leave interest rates unchanged at the August 22 meeting but
investors worried that six hikes in rates in the past year will
have a cumulative effect on corporate earnings.
</P>
<P>
Alcoa led the Dow's advance after the aluminum producer
reported that it gained higher-than-expected earnings in the
second quarter. Rating upgrade of several retailers also helped
drive the blue chip index higher.
</P>
<P>
But Yahoo! fell, dragging the Nasdaq composite lower. The
company is expected to report its second-quarter earnings Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 1.93 at 656.29 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 0.08 at 936.56. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 2.61 at 530.83.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,619 up, 1,240 down and 529
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 814.94 million shares from 929.19
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
