<HEADLINE> Britain's Cook to Attend G8 Foreign Ministers' Meeting In Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook Monday travels to Japan to attend the Group of Eight (G8)
foreign ministers' meeting to be held in Miyazaki from Wednesday
to Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key item on the agenda will be conflict prevention,
including the issue of conflict diamonds, the British Foreign
Office said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Non-proliferation, terrorism, and United Nations reform will
also be discussed. The eight ministers will also consider a number
of regional issues including the Korean Peninsula, South Asia, the
Middle East, the Balkans and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from the eight leading industrialized nations
will also meet representatives from the Non-Aligned Movement, the
Chairs of G77 and the Association of South East Asian Nations.
</P>
<P>
This year's G8 Summit will take place on 21-23 July. Japan
currently holds the G8 presidency and the summit will be in
Okinawa.
</P>
<P>
The members of the G8 leading industrialized nations are
Britain, France, Italy, Germany, Japan, the United States, Canada
and Russia. 
