<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S., Vietnam Close to Trade Pact, Barshefsky Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Trade Representative
Charlene Barshefsky said Monday that the U.S. and Vietnam were
close to finalizing a historic trade pact.
</P>
<P>
"We are very close... but not quite there yet," Barshefsky told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
"So we shall see if this time Vietnam is willing to make the
political commitment to move forward," she said.
</P>
<P>
Barshefsky said talks with Vietnamese Trade Minister Vu Khoan
would continue Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. and Vietnamese trade negotiators kicked off the trade
talks last week in a bid to hammer out details of the proposed
bilateral trade pact, a result of four years of on-and-off
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposed pact, Vietnam would lower its tariffs and
undertake a broad range of measures to open its markets to U.S.
goods, services and investment.
</P>
<P>
In return, Hanoi would get access to the U.S. market under the
same system of low tariffs given to most nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
