<HEADLINE> European Major Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- London and Paris stock markets
closed lower Monday after drifting in and out of negative
territory for most of the session, led by drug high-tech stocks.
</P>
<P>
Drug and computer software stocks dragged London's FTSE 100
lower after a mixed start on Wall Street. The benchmark stock
index closed 31.3 points or 0.48 percent lower at 6,466.2.
</P>
<P>
Computer software group Sema fell 4 percent, Sage Group lost 5
percent, and rival Misys dropped 3.5 percent. However, the biggest
loser was CMG, declining 5.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 300 index fell 0.3 percent to 1,619.76. Its
health-care segment slid 5 percent, due largely to a 4.6-percent
drop for medical science company NAM.
</P>
<P>
The CAC 40 in Paris fell 78.55 points, or 1.2 percent, to 6,487.
42, with Franco-German drug maker Aventis and data network
operator Equant leading declines.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Frankfurt closed slightly higher. Its benchmark Dax
index recovered to close 18.6 or 0.26 percent higher at 7,070.82
points after dipping into negative territory in late session trade.
</P>
</TEXT>
