<HEADLINE> Sao Paulo Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo
Securities Exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed down
Monday with the key Bovespa Index falling by 0.72 percent to 17,
471 points from last Friday's 17,598 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 305 million U.S. dollars against 507 million
dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the local currency, the real, stood at 1.
79 for one U.S. dollar, compared with 1.80 for one dollar last
Friday. 
